Iraq Needs $22 Billion Power Projects by 2015, Zaman Reports

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-06-14T06:13:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/iraq-needs-22-billion-power-projects-by-2015-zaman-reports.html
Iraq  needs about $22 billion of
investment by 2015 to meet electricity production, transmission
and distribution needs,  Zaman  reported, citing Ala’a Disher
Zamil, head of independent projects at Iraq’s ministry of power,
who spoke in a conference in Istanbul yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 